File: Wayde van Niekerk recently returned to training after enduring a number of setbacks. JOHANNESBURG - South African 400m world record holder Wayde van Niekerk has tested positive for the coronavirus. That is according to Italian newspaper La Gazzetta dello Sport. READ: Van Niekerk wins first race this year on comeback trail The 28-year old arrived in Italy in July to prepare for the Triveneto Meeting. Van Niekerk is in quarantine there where he's been training for the new European season. READ: Wayde van Niekerk looks for positives in Tokyo postponement He's been out of action for a while due to an injury he sustained during a celebrity touch rugby match in October 2017.